				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Song lineup to maintain aggro<a name="53977"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 27 04 3:25 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Bard mezz draws as much aggro as bard haste or bard slow, which is pretty darn low. Bards get VERY little aggro directly for song effect. Rather, bard's get aggro as a side effect of the songs. Regen songs gain you healing aggro(on a smaller scale than a cleric, but try singing an AE hp regen during inc on a raid and you will get aggro).
<br />

<br />
Runes that prevent damage also draws aggro, SoS is a good aggro song. When I play tank(which is not often) I twist AE slow with a dot(Melody of Mischeif), group rune(Song of Shielding), and 2 dots. The SoS is a good way to grab aggro back from other group members, DoTs will let you gain aggro slowly over time. I find this to be the best song twist to hold aggro for me.
<br />

<br />
Since most of the content I ever find myself tanking are not charmable, its not really an option, but when dealing with lower level content, charm is by far the best way to gain instant aggro, but you will still need to pump aggro songs afterward or a rogue/monk can take it from you. And remember to break charm quick before the mob regens too much, try to use a self clickie, as your group members may have pets.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"><hr size="1" align="left" width="15%"><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=844375">Reilna Voiceofwar</A><br>

"Be a bard's bard!"</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
