				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Song lineup to maintain aggro<a name="54016"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 27 04 6:46 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Aye, most of our songs are pretty low agro.  The one minute slow songs are both fairly decent though, i reccomend hitting it with the lower one with a DoT component first, and then with req of time (since it overwrites the other, but not vice versa) and then hitting it with 4 regular dots.  Charm songs, even on uncharmables, do some agro, however they drain mana, and it is not noticably more agro than a chant.  Also hit it with RoTime again each time the song refreshes until your agro is solid.  If you are tanking instead of kiting you can try the begging trick, but beg has a very very small radius, smaller than most combat ranges, so move in close or it will do nothing.  Also get fast procing weapons as any tank knows.
<br />

<br />
I usually don't have a set of dots up when i am grouping, but I have either 1 DD or one dot memmed.  To pull add agro off the shammy or cleric or what ever (unless death is an issue, in which case MEZ) I hit it with slow, then 3 DD or dots, and then slow again, while pummeling it.  It usually takes me until the second slow to get agro, pretty pathetic, 20 seconds to steal agro... which is why I say, MEZ if death is an issue.  And btw, I wield 2 delay 19 weapons, one has 2 procs, the other has one, so I proc failrly often.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
