				<td colspan="2"><span>I think the main problem here is level difference.  When you get your chant upgrades it should help. Starting out with a horn and Angstlich's Assonance before switching to drum and chants will get you a bit more aggro. 
<br />

<br />
Some mobs have higher proximity aggro than others. I two-box kite with my shaman when there's nothing better to do. In tatics, the shammy can start dotting from the get go and they don't turn on him. I can toss in malos, bane and a poison dot. But a mage or necro pet picks up aggro. In HoH on the other hand, they don't turn on pets so early, but I have to stick to disease dots. One poison cast and the shaman is history. Even when the mob is near 60%. So you may try switching your targets.
<br />
</span></td>
